                <h1>Does Wallpaper Damage Walls? Find Out!</h1>
                <p>Wallpaper can potentially ruin walls if not applied or removed correctly. Poor adhesion may lead to peeling, bubbles, or mold growth, affecting wall integrity. Removing wallpaper can damage the paint or drywall beneath it, making repairs necessary. Proper preparation and care are essential for a successful wallpaper application and removal.</p>
